title: Java Software Developer
description:
Java Developer (Job Code: J2EE)



• Proficiency in coding in Java 17, Spring Boot technologies, microservices as 

well as unit testing/Mockito experience


• Work on developing framework for microservices to be deployed on AWS, update 

code, create/run CICD pipeline


• Work with product owners and other development team members to determine new 

features and user stories needed in new/revised applications or large/complex 

development projects.


• Create or Update documentation in support of development efforts. Documents 

may include detailed specifications, implementation guides.


• Participate in code reviews with peers and managers to ensure that each increment 

adheres to original vision as described in the user story and all standard resource 

libraries and architecture patterns as appropriate.


• Participate in all agile ceremonies including planning, grooming, product 

demonstration and team retrospectives.
requirements:
• 3 to 6 years of development experience in Java/J2EE technologies
• Strong development experience with Java, Spring boot, Spring Core, Spring 

MVC, Spring Security and REST Web Services is a must.
• Proficiency in unit testing/Mockito as well as coding in Java and Spring Boot 

technologies
• Experience with RDBMS (Oracle / Postgres) & No SQL (Mongo / Document DB)
• Experience with Object-Oriented Design, Design Patterns, and test-driven 

development
• Experience with build tools like Maven/Gradle
• Experience with Jenkins
• Basic familiarity with Angular / React / or NodeJS would be helpful
• Basic familiarity with Cucumber, Selenium
• Knowledge of UNIX (Linux) environment
• Superior time management and work organization
• Strong oral and written communication skills
• Work as a team in a fast-paced agile environment
• Passion for continuous improvement and learning
benefits: Health insurance, Flexible working hours, Learning budget

title: Junior Property Marketing Specialist
description: We are seeking a motivated Junior Property Marketing Specialist to join our real estate team. This role is perfect for recent graduates or early-career professionals looking to break into the real estate industry. You will assist in developing marketing strategies for residential and commercial properties, create engaging content for social media and marketing materials, and support senior team members in client presentations.
requirements:
Bachelor's degree in Marketing, Business, or related field
Fresh graduate or 1-2 years of experience in marketing
Basic knowledge of digital marketing and social media platforms
Strong communication and interpersonal skills
Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite and basic design tools
Willingness to learn and adapt in a fast-paced environment
skills: Digital Marketing, Social Media, Content Creation, Market Research
benefits: Health Insurance, Paid Training, Career Growth Opportunities

title: Mid-Level Real Estate Financial Analyst
description: Join our finance team as a Mid-Level Real Estate Financial Analyst. You will be responsible for conducting financial analysis for property investments, preparing detailed financial models and reports, evaluating market trends and investment opportunities, and collaborating with senior management on strategic decisions. This role requires strong analytical skills and experience in real estate finance.
requirements:
Bachelor's degree in Finance, Economics, or related field
3-5 years of experience in financial analysis, preferably in real estate
Proficiency in Excel, financial modeling, and data analysis
Knowledge of real estate market dynamics and investment principles
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills
Excellent written and verbal communication abilities
skills: Financial Analysis, Excel, Financial Modeling, Market Research, Real Estate Investment
benefits: Health Insurance, Performance Bonus, Professional Development, Flexible Hours

title: Mid-Level Property Operations Manager
description: We are looking for an experienced Mid-Level Property Operations Manager to oversee day-to-day operations of our real estate portfolio. You will manage property maintenance, tenant relations, vendor coordination, and ensure compliance with regulations. The ideal candidate will have experience in property management and strong leadership skills to manage operational teams effectively.
requirements:
Bachelor's degree in Business Administration, Real Estate, or related field
4-6 years of experience in property management or operations
Knowledge of property maintenance, tenant management, and regulatory compliance
Strong leadership and team management skills
Excellent organizational and multitasking abilities
Proficiency in property management software and MS Office
skills: Property Management, Operations Management, Team Leadership, Vendor Management, Compliance
benefits: Health Insurance, Variable Pay, Team Building Activities, Learning Opportunities

title: Mid-Level Real Estate Sales Manager
description: Join our sales team as a Mid-Level Real Estate Sales Manager. You will lead a team of sales agents, develop sales strategies for residential and commercial properties, build and maintain client relationships, and achieve sales targets. This role requires proven sales experience in real estate and strong leadership capabilities to drive team performance.
requirements:
Bachelor's degree in Business, Sales, or related field
4-5 years of experience in real estate sales or related industry
Proven track record of achieving sales targets
Strong leadership and team management skills
Excellent communication and negotiation abilities
Knowledge of real estate market trends and regulations
skills: Sales Management, Team Leadership, Negotiation, Client Relations, Real Estate Market Knowledge
benefits: Health Insurance, Sales Incentives, Commission Structure, Career Advancement

description: We are seeking a Senior Real Estate Development Director to lead our property development initiatives. You will oversee large-scale development projects from conception to completion, manage cross-functional teams, negotiate with stakeholders and government agencies, and develop strategic partnerships. This senior role requires extensive experience in real estate development and strong executive presence.

Master's degree in Real Estate Development, Architecture, Business, or related field
8+ years of experience in real estate development or construction management
Proven experience managing large-scale development projects
Strong knowledge of zoning laws, building codes, and regulatory requirements
Excellent leadership, strategic thinking, and decision-making skills
Strong financial acumen and project management expertise
skills: Real Estate Development, Project Management, Strategic Planning, Stakeholder Management, Regulatory Compliance

description: Join our investment team as a Senior Real Estate Investment Strategist. You will develop and execute investment strategies for our real estate portfolio, conduct comprehensive market analysis and due diligence, manage relationships with investors and partners, and lead investment committee presentations. This senior role requires deep expertise in real estate investment and capital markets.
requirements:
Master's degree in Finance, Real Estate, or MBA from reputed institution
7+ years of experience in real estate investment, private equity, or investment banking
Strong analytical skills with expertise in financial modeling and valuation
Experience with institutional investors and capital raising
Excellent presentation and communication skills
CFA, CPA, or similar professional certification preferred
skills: Investment Strategy, Financial Modeling, Market Analysis, Due Diligence, Capital Markets, Investor Relations
benefits: Health Insurance, Performance Bonus, Stock Options, Executive Perks, Professional Development
